contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

13:24.076 --> 13:26.045
Hey. Just got your text.

13:26.045 --> 13:27.046
Is everything okay?

13:27.046 --> 13:28.614
What did you say to Amy this morning?

13:28.614 --> 13:31.317
What? Me? Nothing. Why do
you think I said something?

13:31.317 --> 13:33.419
You told her I called her uptight.

13:33.419 --> 13:35.054
Oh, yeah. That might have come up.

13:36.355 --> 13:38.057
Riley, she broke up with me.

13:38.057 --> 13:40.059
Oh my God, Danny, I'm sorry.

13:40.059 --> 13:41.894
It just... it just came out.

13:41.894 --> 13:44.664
But honestly, you haven't been
acting like yourself around her.

13:44.664 --> 13:46.732
Why? Because I went to a museum?

13:46.732 --> 13:49.101
No, because you're doing things
that you don't even like to do.

13:49.101 --> 13:51.470
It's because I like her!

13:51.470 --> 13:53.973
That's what you're supposed
to do when you like somebody.

13:53.973 --> 13:56.442
The Riley I know would
understand that and be supportive.

13:56.442 --> 13:58.444
If you keep telling everyone
you're my best friend,

13:58.444 --> 13:59.845
how about you act like it?

14:03.349 --> 14:05.017
(Cellphone ringing)

14:06.852 --> 14:08.454
Bonnie's Beauty Barn.

14:08.454 --> 14:11.090
Congratulations, you just
got one step closer to pretty.

14:14.760 --> 14:17.096
Oh! I would love to.

14:17.096 --> 14:18.931
No no no no, that's perfect.

14:18.931 --> 14:20.066
I'll see you in a few.

14:20.066 --> 14:22.468
- Yow!
- Don't wanna talk about it anymore.

14:22.468 --> 14:23.803
Oh, hey, Danny, guess what?

14:23.803 --> 14:24.970
- I just got my very first client.
- (Door slams)

14:24.970 --> 14:26.372
Danny, I'm so sorry.

14:26.372 --> 14:27.673
Hey, Riles, big news!

14:27.673 --> 14:29.408
- You're never gonna... 
- (Door slams)

14:30.976 --> 14:32.078
- Hey, mom.
- All right, don't you move

14:32.078 --> 14:33.612
until I'm done talking about myself.

14:34.747 --> 14:37.083
I just got my first client.

14:37.083 --> 14:39.418
(Squeals) Where's Emma?

14:39.418 --> 14:40.920
I thought you were picking her up.

14:40.920 --> 14:42.054
No. No, not me.

14:42.054 --> 14:44.423
Well, if you're not, then who is?

14:46.058 --> 14:49.562
- Tucker?
- Oh. Hey, baby lady.

14:49.562 --> 14:50.563
(Tucker chuckles)

14:52.174 --> 14:54.277
Okay, this is a little embarrassing,

14:54.277 --> 14:56.145
but I don't think I can
give you Emma right now.

14:56.145 --> 14:57.280
Oh!

14:57.280 --> 14:59.782
If she needs to be changed,
by all means, take your time.

14:59.782 --> 15:00.983
(Chuckles)

15:00.983 --> 15:04.654
You know, uh, you got
my boy pretty worked up.

15:04.654 --> 15:08.257
Listen, I so don't want to
get in the middle of anything.

15:08.257 --> 15:09.225
Oh, no, you're not.

15:09.225 --> 15:11.193
Look, if you just give
me that girl's number,

15:11.193 --> 15:13.496
I swear she will never
even know where I got it.

15:13.496 --> 15:15.264
- Whose number?
- That nanny's.

15:15.264 --> 15:17.266
- You're looking for a nanny?
- At the end of the day,

15:17.266 --> 15:18.501
who isn't, right?

15:18.501 --> 15:19.502
(Laughing)

15:19.502 --> 15:20.870
Oh, great. You're all here.

15:20.870 --> 15:21.971
Look at us, being civil.

15:21.971 --> 15:24.273
Okay, uh, let's grab Emma and go.

15:24.273 --> 15:26.142
Or better yet, I'll grab Emma

15:26.142 --> 15:27.209
and you go.

15:27.209 --> 15:29.912
Cool. See you at home then.

15:29.912 --> 15:30.913
Wait.

15:30.913 --> 15:32.281
I thought you said he moved out.

15:32.281 --> 15:34.150
What? Why would I move out?

15:34.150 --> 15:36.652
That's life in the big
city. Everyone's on the move.

15:36.652 --> 15:37.987
And shouldn't you be?

15:41.157 --> 15:42.258
What's going on?

15:42.258 --> 15:44.894
Ben, you told me you were a couple.

15:44.894 --> 15:47.263
- A couple of guys raising a baby.
- (Tucker exhales)

15:47.263 --> 15:51.100
You gotta be careful just
tossing that around, Ben.

15:51.100 --> 15:53.235
People will start to think we're gay.

15:55.037 --> 15:57.807
Oh my God! You lied to me?!

15:57.807 --> 16:00.209
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

16:00.209 --> 16:01.711
But Emma really needed daycare,

16:01.711 --> 16:03.713
and you were all "hey, look at my bra."

16:03.713 --> 16:05.748
I showed you my bra!

16:05.748 --> 16:07.249
(Exhales) Oh my God,

16:07.249 --> 16:09.085
why didn't I get to see her bra?

16:10.086 --> 16:11.620
Dude, come on.

16:11.620 --> 16:13.622
Please, is there any possible way we can

16:13.622 --> 16:14.857
just do this again and start over?

16:14.857 --> 16:16.025
Sure.

16:16.025 --> 16:17.159
We're full.

16:17.159 --> 16:18.828
Get your baby and get out.

16:22.798 --> 16:26.602
Hey, that nanny doesn't
think I'm gay, does she?

16:29.105 --> 16:30.239
(Knocks on door)

16:30.239 --> 16:32.875
Amy, it's me, Riley.

16:32.875 --> 16:34.543
I need to talk to you.

16:37.947 --> 16:40.216
I probably wouldn't open
the door to me either.

16:40.216 --> 16:41.917
(Mumbles)

16:41.917 --> 16:44.086
I just came by to apologize.

16:44.086 --> 16:47.089
I'm sorry.

16:47.089 --> 16:49.225
You're right, I am a little jealous.

16:49.225 --> 16:50.926
But I miss my friend.

16:52.128 --> 16:55.498
But more than that, I'm really protective.

16:55.498 --> 16:58.667
I just want everyone to see
Danny the way that I see him,

16:58.667 --> 17:00.903
which... 

17:00.903 --> 17:03.005
is pretty near perfect.

17:03.005 --> 17:05.508
So he really is my hero.

17:05.508 --> 17:08.511
Excuse me, ma'am, is there a problem here?

17:08.511 --> 17:10.512
Oh my God! Super Danny!

17:10.512 --> 17:12.681
What are you doing here?

17:12.681 --> 17:14.150
I came to win back Amy.

17:14.150 --> 17:16.819
But you were right, she
needs to see the real me.

17:16.819 --> 17:18.154
I accepted who she was,

17:18.154 --> 17:19.922
now she needs to accept who I am.

17:19.922 --> 17:23.125
Are you sure you wanna have
this conversation in a unitard?

17:23.125 --> 17:25.094
It's the only way.

17:29.065 --> 17:30.733
Amy, it's me.

17:30.733 --> 17:32.068
We need to talk.

17:32.068 --> 17:33.102
(Screams)

17:33.102 --> 17:34.603
Amy! Stand back!

17:38.707 --> 17:40.176
Oh, my God. Danny.

17:40.176 --> 17:42.144
My door!

17:42.144 --> 17:44.080
I heard you scream. Are you all right?

17:44.080 --> 17:46.082
No. Look at me.

17:46.082 --> 17:48.851
I said sexed up, not jacked up!

17:48.851 --> 17:52.021
F.Y.I., it's customary
to tip as big as the hair.

17:52.021 --> 17:53.522
(Mouthing)

17:53.522 --> 17:55.691
(Sighs deeply) I... 

17:55.691 --> 17:57.860
I was just trying to loosen up a little.

17:57.860 --> 17:59.695
But I like you just the way you are.

17:59.695 --> 18:00.863
You do?

18:00.863 --> 18:03.165
Oh, because I like you just the way... 

18:03.165 --> 18:06.001
Why are you dressed like that?

18:06.001 --> 18:08.170
Because I wanted you to see the real me.

18:08.170 --> 18:11.006
Well, not the real real me.

18:11.006 --> 18:13.075
Can't really fly. Cape's just for show.

18:13.075 --> 18:14.043
(Giggles)

18:14.043 --> 18:16.045
Well, I like everything I see.

18:23.786 --> 18:26.021
Bonnie Wheeler... 

18:26.021 --> 18:28.657
changing lives one head at a time.

18:30.159 --> 18:32.495
I don't just do it... 

18:32.495 --> 18:34.497
I hair-do it.

18:39.034 --> 18:41.770
All right, there you go.

18:41.770 --> 18:42.938
Are you sure you're okay with opening up

18:42.938 --> 18:44.640
Half-O-Ween to outsiders?

18:44.640 --> 18:46.642
Maybe change is a good thing.

18:48.077 --> 18:50.146
- You ready?
- Amy: I think so.

18:50.146 --> 18:52.481
(Door opens)

18:55.050 --> 18:57.686
Okay!

18:57.686 --> 18:59.588
I take back what I said before.

18:59.588 --> 19:01.490
I think I might actually
like this look better.

19:02.825 --> 19:04.493
Mom, just let it go.

19:04.493 --> 19:06.962
Honestly, who gets thrown out of a daycare?

19:06.962 --> 19:08.531
I mean, she's not even one,

19:08.531 --> 19:09.999
and she already has a record.

19:09.999 --> 19:11.500
I'll switch my shifts if I have to.

19:11.500 --> 19:12.968
I'll make it work. I promise.

19:15.037 --> 19:16.872
Yeah?

19:16.872 --> 19:18.040
What do you think?

19:18.040 --> 19:19.909
Okay. (Chuckles)

19:19.909 --> 19:21.544
A mummy... I like it.

19:21.544 --> 19:23.879
Oh, I was going for
"crazy toilet paper guy."

19:23.879 --> 19:25.981
But mummy's better.

19:25.981 --> 19:28.083
(Knocks on door)

19:32.855 --> 19:33.856
Megan?

19:33.856 --> 19:36.859
Um, so not expecting for you to

19:36.859 --> 19:39.695
open the door dressed as... 

19:39.695 --> 19:41.497
What are you exactly?

19:41.497 --> 19:43.832
A kitchen robot.

19:43.832 --> 19:47.002
And of course you know my
trusty sidekick baby bot.

19:47.002 --> 19:48.637
(Robotic voice) Hello, Megan.

19:48.637 --> 19:49.838
(Chuckles weakly)

19:49.838 --> 19:51.140
(Normal voice) We're
going to a costume thing.

19:51.140 --> 19:53.676
I got that.

19:53.676 --> 19:55.678
You forgot Emma's diaper bag.

19:55.678 --> 19:57.546
Uh, you wanna just put it on the table?

19:57.546 --> 19:58.981
Thanks.

20:00.149 --> 20:02.017
All: Hey.

20:02.017 --> 20:03.552
(Door closes)

20:04.987 --> 20:07.790
Again, I'm sorry for lying.

20:07.790 --> 20:09.792
Pretty girls make me do stupid things... 

20:09.792 --> 20:11.026
you and Emma.

20:11.026 --> 20:12.695
Well, I guess

20:12.695 --> 20:14.897
I can't be too mad at a
guy who pretends to be gay

20:14.897 --> 20:17.533
just to get his little
girl into daycare, so... 

20:17.533 --> 20:19.902
So maybe we can start over over?

20:21.604 --> 20:23.072
Hi, I'm Ben Wheeler

20:23.072 --> 20:24.540
and this is Emma.

20:24.540 --> 20:27.176
Crazy, scheme-y, with
a smile I don't trust

20:27.176 --> 20:28.944
and spatulas for hands.

20:30.145 --> 20:31.614
(Robotic voice) I am in.

20:31.614 --> 20:33.048
(Chuckles)

20:33.048 --> 20:36.051
Could I interest you in a costume?

20:36.051 --> 20:37.653
I've got more tinfoil.

20:37.653 --> 20:39.555
(Chuckling) Okay.

20:41.991 --> 20:43.559
Mmm!

20:46.208 --> 20:48.210
To another successful adventure.

20:51.580 --> 20:53.616
You really are my hero, Wheeler.

20:53.616 --> 20:56.218
Do you think we're
getting too old for this?

20:56.218 --> 20:58.621
You're never too old to be yourself, right?

20:58.621 --> 21:01.624
So now that we've opened it up... 

21:01.624 --> 21:03.092
you think Half-O-Ween might catch on?

21:03.092 --> 21:04.593
Not a chance.

21:04.593 --> 21:05.561
And do we care?

21:05.561 --> 21:06.796
Not a bit.

21:09.098 --> 21:12.101
(Both in deep voice)
Happy Half-oO-Wween, New York!

